SCP 2021 Presentation

Laurent Gatto and Christophe Vanderaa, UCLouvain

SCP2021 - 16 August 2021

Link to this page: http://bit.ly/202108SCP

Talk material

Our talk Mass Spectrometry-Based Single-Cell Proteomics Data Analysis at SCP2021 is composed of 4 parts:

  1. What is scp is a general introduction to the scp package, how test it, and where to find help and more information.

  2. Handling quantitative proteomics features? demonstrating the managing of quantitative proteomcis features.

  3. Importing single-cell proteomics data explains how to load data as a QFeatures object, listing requirements and showing a real-case example.

  4. Data processing with scp describes some single-cell processing steps.

Further reading

  • Vanderaa and Gatto, Utilizing scp for the analysis and replication of single-cell proteomics data 2021.

  • scp webpage and vignettes: https://UCLouvain-CBIO.github.io/scp

  • QFeatures webpage and vignettes: https://RforMassSpectrometry.github.io/QFeatures
